5
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:07,401
Tim Cook:
Good morning, and welcome to WWDC.

6
00:01:07,434 --> 00:01:09,203
We have a big day of announcements

7
00:01:09,236 --> 00:01:12,339
about our latest technologies
and platforms.

8
00:01:12,372 --> 00:01:14,942
These platforms,
and the products they drive,

9
00:01:14,975 --> 00:01:18,178
deliver amazing experiences for our users

10
00:01:18,212 --> 00:01:21,682
and provide developers
with incredible opportunities

11
00:01:21,715 --> 00:01:25,452
so they can use their superpowers
to innovate, create,

12
00:01:25,485 --> 00:01:30,624
and collaborate, making apps
that continue to change the world.

13
00:01:30,657 --> 00:01:34,027
And WWDC is designed
to give this community

14
00:01:34,061 --> 00:01:37,531
what they need to do their very best work.

15
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:41,268
We love to support our developers
beyond WWDC

16
00:01:41,301 --> 00:01:46,874
with comprehensive world-class support
and other important initiatives.

17
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:51,445
We just opened our brand-new
Developers Center across from Apple Park

18
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:54,448
where developers can engage
with our engineers.

19
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:56,884
And to reach our global community,

20
00:01:56,917 --> 00:02:01,955
this past fall we introduced our first
online Tech Talks for developers

21
00:02:01,989 --> 00:02:04,825
to learn more about our new technologies

22
00:02:04,858 --> 00:02:07,361
and directly connect with Apple engineers

23
00:02:07,394 --> 00:02:11,231
in live sessions
and one-on-one office hours.

24
00:02:12,366 --> 00:02:16,637
We are also committed to cultivating
the next generation of developers,

25
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:20,841
including efforts to reach
underrepresented communities.

26
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:25,145
So our developer academies teach
students the fundamentals of coding

27
00:02:25,179 --> 00:02:27,247
as well as the other necessary skills

28
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:31,318
to find and create jobs
in the app economy.

29
00:02:31,351 --> 00:02:33,387
There are 17 around the world

30
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:37,057
including the academy in Detroit
we founded in October

31
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:41,695
as a part of Apple's Racial Equity
and Justice Initiative.

32
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:47,634
And in Saudi Arabia, we launched our first
developer academy for women in February.

33
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:52,339
Our Entrepreneur Camps provide developers
from underrepresented communities

34
00:02:52,372 --> 00:02:56,610
with mentorship, inspiration,
and insights from Apple.

35
00:02:56,643 --> 00:03:00,581
The first camps were for female founders,
and this past year,

36
00:03:00,614 --> 00:03:04,718
we expanded the camps
to reach Black and Latin founders.

37
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:07,921
Alumni have gone on
to secure major funding

38
00:03:07,955 --> 00:03:10,724
and see great success on the App Store.

39
00:03:12,059 --> 00:03:16,129
These ongoing efforts empower
all developers with the tools,

40
00:03:16,163 --> 00:03:20,434
technologies, and inspiration
to change the world for the better.

41
00:03:21,301 --> 00:03:26,473
Last year, many millions of developers
engaged in WWDC,

42
00:03:26,507 --> 00:03:30,644
and we expect millions more
to join us again this year.

43
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:34,781
In fact, we're excited to say
we've grown our developer community

44
00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:38,886
to over 34 million Apple developers.

45
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:43,590
We have a huge week ahead of us,
with an amazing online experience,

46
00:03:43,624 --> 00:03:47,628
including sessions, labs,
and digital lounges,

47
00:03:47,661 --> 00:03:51,965
which will all be available for free
to our developers.

48
00:03:51,999 --> 00:03:55,269
Today, we're going to push
our platforms further than ever

49
00:03:55,302 --> 00:03:58,005
for our developers and our users.

50
00:03:58,038 --> 00:04:02,176
So let's get started
by sending it over to Craig.

51
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:10,217
♪ ♪

52
00:04:14,488 --> 00:04:17,424
Craig Federighi: I'm really excited about
what we have to show you today.

53
00:04:17,457 --> 00:04:20,093
But first, let's head downstairs.

54
00:04:20,127 --> 00:04:27,134
♪ ♪

55
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:40,247
♪ ♪

56
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:44,751
Now, let's talk about iOS.

57
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:48,755
Together with iPhone,
iOS helps you get so much done,

58
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:51,091
whether you're at home or on the move.

59
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,962
And the next release, iOS 16,
offers new intelligence,

60
00:04:54,995 --> 00:04:58,332
sharing, and communication features
that are going to enhance

61
00:04:58,365 --> 00:05:01,468
so much of what you do with your iPhone.

62
00:05:01,502 --> 00:05:05,939
And those come together with an incredible
set of new personalization features

63
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:10,777
that will make your experience
feel fresh and completely you.

64
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:14,381
Let's get started
with the all-new Lock Screen.

65
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:18,685
The Lock Screen is the first thing you see
every time you pick up your iPhone.

66
00:05:18,719 --> 00:05:21,154
It's a place where you can check
the date and time,

67
00:05:21,188 --> 00:05:22,823
look out for key messages,

68
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,492
and launch the camera
to quickly capture the moment.

69
00:05:25,526 --> 00:05:28,996
And it's just as much
a place for personalization,

70
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:33,367
where so many of you put a photo
that makes iPhone uniquely yours.

71
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:38,639
In iOS 16, we're bringing the biggest
update ever to the Lock Screen,

72
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:42,643
completely reimagining
how it looks and works for you.

73
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:43,977
Let's take a look.

74
00:05:44,778 --> 00:05:52,786
♪ ♪

75
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:09,803
♪ ♪

76
00:06:15,809 --> 00:06:23,817
♪ ♪

77
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:28,488
Craig: The new Lock Screen remains
undeniably iPhone,

78
00:06:28,522 --> 00:06:31,358
while also giving you new ways
to make it more personal,

79
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,760
beautiful, and helpful than ever.

80
00:06:33,794 --> 00:06:35,495
Let me show you.

81
00:06:35,529 --> 00:06:37,030
Here's my Lock Screen.

82
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:39,266
You'll notice the subtle depth effect

83
00:06:39,299 --> 00:06:41,668
with my daughters appearing
in front of the time.

84
00:06:41,702 --> 00:06:43,036
I really love it.

85
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:47,541
Now, if I just press and hold,
I can personalize it further.

86
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,377
I'll just tap Customize,
and now I'm in the editor.

87
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,678
Now, check this out.

88
00:06:51,712 --> 00:06:55,549
I can simply swipe
to try out different styles

89
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:59,286
that automatically change
the color filter, the background,

90
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:02,756
and the font for the time,
all to complement each other.

91
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:04,324
These look really beautiful.

92
00:07:04,358 --> 00:07:06,126
So let's go with this one.

93
00:07:06,159 --> 00:07:09,062
Now, of course,
if I want to change anything,

94
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:12,933
it's easy to dial it in further
to get it just the way I want it.

95
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:17,304
All I need to do is tap on any element
of the Lock Screen to start editing.

96
00:07:17,337 --> 00:07:19,406
So let's customize the font.

97
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,009
I can audition different typefaces

98
00:07:22,042 --> 00:07:25,045
and choose from different colors.

99
00:07:25,078 --> 00:07:28,182
And I like this color.
I'll just adjust the shade a little bit.

100
00:07:28,215 --> 00:07:30,384
I think this looks awesome now.

101
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:33,253
Now, I can also make my Lock Screen
more helpful

102
00:07:33,287 --> 00:07:35,822
by putting widgets
right on the Lock Screen.

103
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:38,125
So let me move the girls down here

104
00:07:38,158 --> 00:07:41,361
and tap in to bring up the widget gallery.

105
00:07:41,395 --> 00:07:44,831
And these are really useful
for getting information at a glance,

106
00:07:44,865 --> 00:07:46,333
like upcoming calendar events.

107
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:49,837
So I'll add the temperature,

108
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:54,441
my Activity rings,
and let's drag in the calendar widget.

109
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:56,043
Now, this is great.

110
00:07:56,076 --> 00:08:00,414
And what's even better is,
I'm not limited to just one.

111
00:08:00,447 --> 00:08:02,683
Let's create another.

112
00:08:02,716 --> 00:08:04,985
I can bring up
our brand-new wallpaper gallery,

113
00:08:05,018 --> 00:08:08,589
which showcases
a bunch of options for inspiration.

114
00:08:08,622 --> 00:08:10,524
And there are plenty to choose from here.

115
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:15,395
So much room for personalization,
with millions of combinations.

116
00:08:15,429 --> 00:08:20,100
With Photo Shuffle, I can choose a set
of photos to shuffle throughout the day,

117
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:22,736
And we also have Suggested Photos,

118
00:08:22,769 --> 00:08:25,506
intelligently curated
from my personal library,

119
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:29,042
like the best shots of family
that look great on the Lock Screen.

120
00:08:29,076 --> 00:08:32,846
Now, this is an awesome one
to add to my collection.

121
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:35,516
Now, I've created
a bunch of other Lock Screens,

122
00:08:35,549 --> 00:08:39,152
and by simply swiping,
I can switch between them.

123
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:41,221
It's amazing the range you can create.

124
00:08:41,255 --> 00:08:44,458
Here's Weather,
which shows live weather conditions

125
00:08:44,491 --> 00:08:46,560
like a downpour and lightning.

126
00:08:46,593 --> 00:08:48,595
I just love this animation.

127
00:08:48,629 --> 00:08:50,998
Here's a really cool emoji wallpaper

128
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:53,300
and our Pride wallpaper.

129
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:56,103
And here's one
from our Astronomy collection.

130
00:08:56,136 --> 00:09:00,908
Watch how it animates fluidly
as I swipe into the Home Screen.

131
00:09:00,941 --> 00:09:02,242
So cool.

132
00:09:02,276 --> 00:09:06,780
So that's a quick look
at the all-new Lock Screen.

133
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:09,917
And for developers,
WidgetKit makes it quick and easy

134
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:13,520
to put glanceable information
from their app here as well.

135
00:09:14,121 --> 00:09:17,491
The new Lock Screen is so beautiful,
we wanted to make sure

136
00:09:17,524 --> 00:09:21,962
that you can always enjoy it,
even if you get a lot of notifications.

137
00:09:22,563 --> 00:09:25,766
Sometimes, notifications can
cover up your personal photo.

138
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:28,769
So we've rethought how they appear.

139
00:09:28,802 --> 00:09:33,073
Notifications now roll in from the bottom
of the Lock Screen as you receive them,

140
00:09:33,106 --> 00:09:35,342
and you can choose to hide them
throughout the day.

141
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:38,946
Now, sometimes you get
a bunch of notifications from an app,

142
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:41,782
like when you're following
the score of a basketball game.

143
00:09:41,815 --> 00:09:44,451
Well, now
there's a better way to keep tabs

144
00:09:44,484 --> 00:09:47,855
with something called Live Activities.

145
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:50,691
Live Activities make it easier
to stay on top of things

146
00:09:50,724 --> 00:09:54,828
that are happening in real time
right from your Lock Screen.

147
00:09:54,862 --> 00:09:58,832
And for developers, starting in an update
to iOS 16 later this year,

148
00:09:58,866 --> 00:10:01,368
they can use the Live Activities API

149
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:05,138
to create these compact
and glanceable experiences.

150
00:10:05,172 --> 00:10:08,475
This will make it really easy
to follow that NBA game,

151
00:10:08,509 --> 00:10:10,878
track the progress of an Uber ride,

152
00:10:10,911 --> 00:10:14,481
see how you're doing
on your workout, and more,

153
00:10:14,515 --> 00:10:18,185
all while letting the other elements
on the Lock Screen shine.

154
00:10:18,218 --> 00:10:22,589
One of the most popular activities
for many of us is listening to music.

155
00:10:22,623 --> 00:10:26,126
And now with Live Activities,
the Now Playing controls can expand

156
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:30,664
to a full screen view that celebrates
album art while you listen along.

157
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:34,201
So that's the all-new Lock Screen.

158
00:10:34,234 --> 00:10:37,304
There are some really powerful ways
these updates tie together

159
00:10:37,337 --> 00:10:41,141
and build upon what we introduced
last year with Focus.

160
00:10:41,175 --> 00:10:45,412
Focus has helped people reduce
distractions and stay in the moment.

161
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:47,848
And this year, we're taking it further,

162
00:10:47,881 --> 00:10:51,151
starting with extending Focus
to your Lock Screen.

163
00:10:51,185 --> 00:10:54,388
This means your choice
of a photo and widgets

164
00:10:54,421 --> 00:10:56,924
can all be tied to a particular Focus.

165
00:10:56,957 --> 00:10:59,526
And now that you can have
multiple Lock Screens,

166
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:03,130
you can match them to the appropriate
Focus throughout your day.

167
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:06,433
You can have a dedicated one
for when you're in a Work Focus,

168
00:11:06,466 --> 00:11:09,369
with widgets showing your upcoming meeting
or to-do list.

169
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:13,340
Or, with just a swipe,
you can activate your Personal Focus.

170
00:11:13,373 --> 00:11:16,243
All of your corresponding
notification settings apply,

171
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:19,246
and it extends to your Home Screen too.

172
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:21,982
So now you can elevate
your favorite apps or widgets

173
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,885
for keeping up with friends and family.

174
00:11:24,918 --> 00:11:28,822
And now, your Focus can also carry
into the apps themselves,

175
00:11:28,856 --> 00:11:33,160
with Focus filters, which let you
filter out distracting content.

176
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:35,162
Let's take Safari, for example.

177
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,497
Instead of seeing all of your websites,

178
00:11:37,531 --> 00:11:42,069
you can turn on the Work Focus filter
and see only the tabs that relate to work.

179
00:11:42,102 --> 00:11:45,606
And you can filter
not just tab groups in Safari,

180
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:50,878
but also conversations in Messages,
accounts in Mail, and events in Calendar.

181
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:53,046
And for developers, we have a new API

182
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:56,316
so they can help you focus
in their apps as well.

183
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:59,353
These updates to Focus
can help you draw boundaries

184
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:02,823
and find balance throughout
all of the moments in your life.

185
00:12:02,856 --> 00:12:07,127
Now, let's talk about
what's in store for Messages.

186
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:11,164
Hundreds of millions of people
rely on Messages every single day.

187
00:12:11,198 --> 00:12:15,502
It's integral to how we communicate
with the people who matter most.

188
00:12:15,536 --> 00:12:20,040
And now, we're adding three of the most
highly-requested features to Messages.

189
00:12:20,807 --> 00:12:24,778
First, have you ever sent a Message
only to immediately realize

190
00:12:24,811 --> 00:12:27,214
you didn't quite say what you intended?

191
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:28,315
Well, no worries.

192
00:12:28,348 --> 00:12:31,919
Because now you can edit
any message you just sent

193
00:12:31,952 --> 00:12:35,589
so embarrassing typos
can be a thing of the past.

194
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:39,927
Second, have you ever wished
you'd never sent that message at all?

195
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:43,096
Well, good news–now you have undo send,

196
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:46,500
so you can immediately recall
a recent misfire.

197
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:50,237
And finally, you can now mark
any thread as unread,

198
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:52,973
a perfect tool if you don't have time
to respond in the moment

199
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:56,276
and want to be sure
to come back to a message later.

200
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:59,079
These three features are going to make
a big difference

201
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:01,515
in how you use Messages every single day.

202
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:07,888
Messages makes texting easy and efficient,
and it's also a great way to share.

203
00:13:07,921 --> 00:13:13,527
Last year, we introduced Shared with You,
which takes things like photos, links,

204
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:17,064
and music that your friends share
with you in Messages and highlights them

205
00:13:17,097 --> 00:13:20,300
right in the app
where you'd like to enjoy them later.

206
00:13:20,334 --> 00:13:22,569
And for developers, we're really excited

207
00:13:22,603 --> 00:13:25,539
to make Shared with You
available with a new API.

208
00:13:25,572 --> 00:13:29,276
So when someone sends you a funny video,
a worthwhile article,

209
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:32,246
or a recipe that you don't have time
to check out in the moment,

210
00:13:32,279 --> 00:13:35,582
it'll be there waiting for you
the next time you open that app.

211
00:13:36,216 --> 00:13:41,388
And when it comes to sharing in real time
with others, people are loving SharePlay.

212
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:43,857
It's stellar for enjoying
shared experiences

213
00:13:43,891 --> 00:13:45,692
while connecting over FaceTime.

214
00:13:45,726 --> 00:13:48,495
Like watching TV shows,
listening to music,

215
00:13:48,529 --> 00:13:51,832
or breaking a sweat
to a synced up workout.

216
00:13:51,865 --> 00:13:54,434
So many of your favorite apps
are using SharePlay

217
00:13:54,468 --> 00:13:56,136
to create shared experiences,

218
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:59,473
like listening to bedtime stories together
with Better Sleep

219
00:13:59,506 --> 00:14:03,443
or playing a rowdy game of Heads Up,
no matter how far apart you are.

220
00:14:03,477 --> 00:14:06,213
And this year,
we're making it easier to discover

221
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:10,417
all of these awesome SharePlay experiences
from within your FaceTime call.

222
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:13,754
With just a tap, you can jump
into SharePlay-supported apps

223
00:14:13,787 --> 00:14:17,491
that you already have on your phone,
or discover new experiences

224
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:19,193
that you can share with your friends.

225
00:14:19,226 --> 00:14:22,963
And to give you more opportunities
to enjoy shared experiences,

226
00:14:22,996 --> 00:14:27,768
we're extending SharePlay beyond FaceTime
and bringing it to Messages.

227
00:14:27,801 --> 00:14:30,804
This was the number one request
from developers.

228
00:14:30,838 --> 00:14:32,840
Now when you find something
you want to share,

229
00:14:32,873 --> 00:14:37,077
like a movie on Disney+,
you can kick off SharePlay right there

230
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:40,047
and enjoy it together
while chatting in Messages.

231
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,317
You can watch in sync,
and you've got the same instantaneous

232
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:46,653
shared playback controls
that make SharePlay magical.

233
00:14:46,687 --> 00:14:50,090
So whether you're using SharePlay
for your weekly movie night

234
00:14:50,123 --> 00:14:52,926
or marking a message unread
so you can respond later,

235
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:56,897
Messages has everything you need
to connect with ease.

236
00:14:56,930 --> 00:15:00,701
And we're making it that much easier
to compose Messages

237
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:03,103
with some updates to Dictation.

238
00:15:03,136 --> 00:15:05,572
To tell you more, here's Robby.

239
00:15:08,475 --> 00:15:11,245
Robby Walker:
