your iCloud+ subscription with everyone.

474
00:29:09,183 --> 00:29:14,655
So those are some of the helpful updates
to Family Sharing this year.

475
00:29:14,688 --> 00:29:17,558
Now, as we all know, one of the things

476
00:29:17,591 --> 00:29:21,028
everyone enjoys sharing
with their family is photos.

477
00:29:21,061 --> 00:29:25,899
So this year, we're introducing a better
way to share photos with your family.

478
00:29:25,933 --> 00:29:29,503
Our precious memories are
often captured by several people

479
00:29:29,536 --> 00:29:34,208
and in between personal photos of hobbies,
house projects, and homework,

480
00:29:34,241 --> 00:29:38,212
we have photos on our device that
everyone in the family would like to have.

481
00:29:38,245 --> 00:29:39,713
But no one has all of them,

482
00:29:39,746 --> 00:29:42,783
so the family's memories
are never complete.

483
00:29:42,816 --> 00:29:44,084
Until now.

484
00:29:44,117 --> 00:29:47,421
We're introducing
iCloud Shared Photo Library

485
00:29:47,454 --> 00:29:51,158
to help you share photos seamlessly
and even automatically.

486
00:29:51,191 --> 00:29:52,559
It's easy to set up.

487
00:29:52,593 --> 00:29:55,829
It's a separate iCloud library
that everyone can contribute to,

488
00:29:55,863 --> 00:29:58,232
collaborate on, and enjoy.

489
00:29:58,265 --> 00:30:00,200
You can participate in one shared library

490
00:30:00,234 --> 00:30:02,636
that's shared
with up to five other people.

491
00:30:02,669 --> 00:30:05,939
We've made it simple to share just
the photos you want from your library.

492
00:30:05,973 --> 00:30:08,809
You can share everything
already in your library,

493
00:30:08,842 --> 00:30:12,980
or choose what to include based on
a start date or the people in the photos.

494
00:30:13,013 --> 00:30:15,682
For example, you can choose
to include just the photos

495
00:30:15,716 --> 00:30:18,418
where you were together with your partner
and the kids.

496
00:30:18,452 --> 00:30:20,320
Once the Shared Library is set up,

497
00:30:20,354 --> 00:30:23,857
you can manually move over new photos
after you take them.

498
00:30:23,891 --> 00:30:27,861
But we wanted to make it even easier
with a new switch right in Camera

499
00:30:27,895 --> 00:30:31,632
that sends shots straight to
the Shared Library as you take them.

500
00:30:31,665 --> 00:30:34,868
This is great when you're on a vacation
and you want to make sure

501
00:30:34,902 --> 00:30:37,504
the photos are shared right away.

502
00:30:37,538 --> 00:30:40,240
And if you take a photo
of something personal, like a gift,

503
00:30:40,274 --> 00:30:42,142
you can easily turn it off.

504
00:30:42,176 --> 00:30:45,846
You can also choose to have
the sharing switch enabled automatically

505
00:30:45,879 --> 00:30:49,783
whenever you take shots with other
members of the Shared Library nearby.

506
00:30:49,816 --> 00:30:53,120
So if you take photos on a camping trip,
you don't have to remember

507
00:30:53,153 --> 00:30:54,688
to share them later.

508
00:30:54,721 --> 00:30:59,059
You'll also receive intelligent
sharing suggestions in the For You tab.

509
00:30:59,092 --> 00:31:01,929
Everyone has equal permissions
for adding, editing,

510
00:31:01,962 --> 00:31:04,331
and deleting photos in the Shared Library.

511
00:31:04,364 --> 00:31:07,167
So if one member of the group
is a talented photo editor,

512
00:31:07,201 --> 00:31:10,337
everyone gets to enjoy their edits
to the shared photos.

513
00:31:10,370 --> 00:31:13,073
Deletions, captions,
and keywords sync too.

514
00:31:13,106 --> 00:31:16,810
Content in the Shared Library
will appear in everyone's Memories,

515
00:31:16,844 --> 00:31:19,646
Featured Photos, and in the Photos widget.

516
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:23,851
So you can relive your family's adventures
that include all the photos.

517
00:31:23,884 --> 00:31:26,954
That's iCloud Shared Photo Library:

518
00:31:26,987 --> 00:31:29,690
the best way to share photos
with your family.

519
00:31:29,723 --> 00:31:33,360
And last, let's talk about privacy.

520
00:31:33,393 --> 00:31:37,798
We're always working hard to protect
our users and their privacy,

521
00:31:37,831 --> 00:31:41,969
with features like App Privacy Report,
Mail Privacy Protection,

522
00:31:42,002 --> 00:31:45,339
App Tracking Transparency,
Privacy Nutrition Labels,

523
00:31:45,372 --> 00:31:47,107
and so many more.

524
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:52,079
Another critically important area
is protecting our users' personal safety.

525
00:31:52,112 --> 00:31:54,681
One way we're doing that
is by adding a new tool

526
00:31:54,715 --> 00:31:57,451
to help people quickly turn off
others' access,

527
00:31:57,484 --> 00:32:02,222
for example, disabling location sharing if
they're escaping an abusive relationship.

528
00:32:02,256 --> 00:32:04,358
It's called Safety Check.

529
00:32:04,391 --> 00:32:06,660
To tell you about it, here's Katie.

530
00:32:10,397 --> 00:32:12,266
Katie Skinner:
Many people share passwords

531
00:32:12,299 --> 00:32:14,902
and access to their devices
with their partner.

532
00:32:14,935 --> 00:32:19,273
However, in abusive relationships,
this can threaten personal safety

533
00:32:19,306 --> 00:32:22,376
and make it harder for victims
to get help.

534
00:32:22,409 --> 00:32:24,978
We've been working closely
with organizations

535
00:32:25,012 --> 00:32:28,949
that support victims of domestic
and intimate partner violence.

536
00:32:28,982 --> 00:32:32,953
And the result of those conversations
is Safety Check,

537
00:32:32,986 --> 00:32:37,691
a new section in Settings where you can
quickly review and reset the access

538
00:32:37,724 --> 00:32:39,159
you've granted others.

539
00:32:39,193 --> 00:32:44,364
This lets people in abusive situations
quickly revoke an abuser's access

540
00:32:44,398 --> 00:32:45,966
to their data and location,

541
00:32:45,999 --> 00:32:49,803
enabling them to cut ties
and get to safety.

542
00:32:49,837 --> 00:32:54,308
Safety Check stops sharing your location
with others via FindMy

543
00:32:54,341 --> 00:32:59,079
and resets the system privacy
permissions for all apps.

544
00:32:59,112 --> 00:33:03,584
It also protects access to your messages
by helping you sign out of iCloud

545
00:33:03,617 --> 00:33:05,953
on all your other devices

546
00:33:05,986 --> 00:33:09,356
and restricts Messages and FaceTime
to the device in your hand.

547
00:33:10,791 --> 00:33:14,761
Safety Check also helps you manage
who you've given access to.

548
00:33:14,795 --> 00:33:18,498
And you can audit which permissions
you've granted to certain apps.

549
00:33:18,532 --> 00:33:22,202
We've received some really positive
feedback on our approach,

550
00:33:22,236 --> 00:33:25,005
including from
the National Center for Victims of Crime

551
00:33:25,038 --> 00:33:28,408
who said: "In times of crisis,
for many survivors,

552
00:33:28,442 --> 00:33:32,646
"it's important to know
who has their information and location.

553
00:33:32,679 --> 00:33:36,216
Safety Check helps
give control back to survivors."

554
00:33:36,250 --> 00:33:38,252
This is important work,

555
00:33:38,285 --> 00:33:42,256
expanding the ways
iOS helps you stay safe.

556
00:33:42,289 --> 00:33:44,992
Now, back to you, Craig.

557
00:33:45,025 --> 00:33:48,595
Craig: Protecting you and your privacy
is and will always be

558
00:33:48,629 --> 00:33:51,465
at the center of what we do.

559
00:33:51,498 --> 00:33:57,738
iOS 16 offers so many updates that will
change the way you experience iPhone.

560
00:33:57,771 --> 00:34:00,741
iOS also extends that experience
beyond the phone,

561
00:34:00,774 --> 00:34:03,877
to enhance how you interact
with the world around you.

562
00:34:03,911 --> 00:34:06,313
Whether helping you through
your morning routine

563
00:34:06,346 --> 00:34:08,982
or keeping you connected
on your next road trip,

564
00:34:09,016 --> 00:34:11,552
iOS has you covered.

