01:37:37,191 --> 01:37:40,227
Tens of thousands of games
use Game Center to help us

1646
01:37:40,260 --> 01:37:43,430
play with our friends
or compete against each other.

1647
01:37:43,463 --> 01:37:47,501
It's easy to jump right in and play
without creating a new account,

1648
01:37:47,534 --> 01:37:50,170
using your Game Center profile.

1649
01:37:50,204 --> 01:37:54,107
You can find friends to play with,
compare scores on leaderboards,

1650
01:37:54,141 --> 01:37:56,643
and track progress through achievements.

1651
01:37:56,677 --> 01:38:00,747
And now, we're bringing Activity
to the Game Center dashboard.

1652
01:38:00,781 --> 01:38:04,184
You can see what your friends are playing,
highlights of their achievements,

1653
01:38:04,218 --> 01:38:06,854
and even find out
when they beat your high score,

1654
01:38:06,887 --> 01:38:10,057
so you know when it's time
to take your game to the next level

1655
01:38:10,090 --> 01:38:11,992
and get back on top.

1656
01:38:12,025 --> 01:38:15,929
And all of this activity appears
on your Game Center profile.

1657
01:38:15,963 --> 01:38:19,800
Game Center has always supported
playing together in real time.

1658
01:38:19,833 --> 01:38:24,104
Now, SharePlay makes it simple
to join and play.

1659
01:38:24,137 --> 01:38:26,473
In a multiplayer game using Game Center,

1660
01:38:26,507 --> 01:38:31,111
just start a SharePlay session
and bring your friends right in.

1661
01:38:31,144 --> 01:38:34,114
These new Game Center features
will be coming to an update

1662
01:38:34,147 --> 01:38:37,117
to iPadOS 16 later this year,

1663
01:38:37,150 --> 01:38:41,088
and we're also bringing them
to iOS and macOS.

1664
01:38:41,121 --> 01:38:45,359
The versatility of iPad
makes it great for so many things,

1665
01:38:45,392 --> 01:38:48,262
and a big part of that is apps.

1666
01:38:48,295 --> 01:38:52,900
This year, we're continuing our work
to make iPad apps more capable

1667
01:38:52,933 --> 01:38:55,869
with desktop-class apps.

1668
01:38:55,903 --> 01:38:59,306
While many iPad apps
have their origins in iOS,

1669
01:38:59,339 --> 01:39:03,410
over the years, they've taken on
their own unique capabilities,

1670
01:39:03,443 --> 01:39:06,947
optimized for the iPad's larger display.

1671
01:39:06,980 --> 01:39:10,817
In iPadOS 16,
we scoured the entire system,

1672
01:39:10,851 --> 01:39:13,353
adding enhancements across the board,

1673
01:39:13,387 --> 01:39:15,722
from system elements and interactions

1674
01:39:15,756 --> 01:39:19,960
to new features you use on Mac
and want on iPad.

1675
01:39:19,993 --> 01:39:21,862
Let me highlight a few of them.

1676
01:39:21,895 --> 01:39:24,565
Undo/redo across the system,

1677
01:39:24,598 --> 01:39:26,867
availability view in Calendar,

1678
01:39:26,900 --> 01:39:30,904
find and merge cards
and create lists in Contacts,

1679
01:39:30,938 --> 01:39:33,073
and we have a big update to Files,

1680
01:39:33,106 --> 01:39:35,108
with some of the most requested features,

1681
01:39:35,142 --> 01:39:37,611
such as the ability to change
file extensions,

1682
01:39:37,644 --> 01:39:40,247
view folder size, and more.

1683
01:39:40,280 --> 01:39:45,018
We've also added system-wide features
that deliver improvements across apps,

1684
01:39:45,052 --> 01:39:48,021
starting with a redesigned
find and replace experience

1685
01:39:48,055 --> 01:39:50,023
that works in-line.

1686
01:39:50,057 --> 01:39:53,861
A document menu in apps
like Files, Pages, and Keynote

1687
01:39:53,894 --> 01:39:56,196
that reveals common actions
you may want to take,

1688
01:39:56,230 --> 01:39:59,900
such as duplicate,
rename, export, and print.

1689
01:39:59,933 --> 01:40:04,905
And for the first time ever,
customizable toolbars in iPadOS

1690
01:40:04,938 --> 01:40:08,208
so you can add the tools
that matter to you most.

1691
01:40:08,242 --> 01:40:11,311
And for developers,
we've created new APIs,

1692
01:40:11,345 --> 01:40:15,315
so they can build these capabilities
right into their own apps.

1693
01:40:15,349 --> 01:40:18,418
These features will help you
be more productive.

1694
01:40:18,452 --> 01:40:20,988
And we have another feature
for Mac that will be great

1695
01:40:21,021 --> 01:40:23,123
for creative pros on iPad.

1696
01:40:23,156 --> 01:40:25,492
And that is reference color.

1697
01:40:25,526 --> 01:40:30,097
The Liquid Retina XDR display
in our latest 12.9-inch iPad Pro

1698
01:40:30,130 --> 01:40:33,267
is great for professional color workflows.

1699
01:40:33,300 --> 01:40:37,638
And with iPadOS 16,
we're introducing Reference Mode,

1700
01:40:37,671 --> 01:40:41,575
which meets the color requirements
in workflows like review and approve,

1701
01:40:41,608 --> 01:40:43,710
color grading, and compositing,

1702
01:40:43,744 --> 01:40:47,748
where accurate colors
and consistent image quality are critical.

1703
01:40:47,781 --> 01:40:51,485
So whether you prefer using iPad Pro
as a standalone device

1704
01:40:51,518 --> 01:40:54,087
or as a second display with Sidecar,

1705
01:40:54,121 --> 01:40:57,624
Reference Mode provides
a consistent reference workflow

1706
01:40:57,658 --> 01:40:59,293
across your pro devices,

1707
01:40:59,326 --> 01:41:04,398
making iPad Pro an indispensable tool
for creative professionals.

1708
01:41:04,431 --> 01:41:07,734
Now, I want to turn our attention
to a set of features

1709
01:41:07,768 --> 01:41:10,838
enabled by the performance of the M1 chip

1710
01:41:10,871 --> 01:41:14,374
in our latest iPad Pro and iPad Air.

1711
01:41:14,408 --> 01:41:19,880
Features for people who push
the versatility of iPad to the limit.

1712
01:41:19,913 --> 01:41:22,916
Pros are always wanting
more space to work with,

1713
01:41:22,950 --> 01:41:26,253
so we're adding
a new display scaling setting,

1714
01:41:26,286 --> 01:41:29,623
which allows you to increase
the pixel density of the display

1715
01:41:29,656 --> 01:41:31,525
so you can view more in your apps,

1716
01:41:31,558 --> 01:41:34,795
which is particularly helpful
when using Split View.

1717
01:41:34,828 --> 01:41:38,065
We also want to enable you
to do more in apps.

1718
01:41:38,098 --> 01:41:40,000
Our latest iPad Air and iPad Pro

1719
01:41:40,033 --> 01:41:44,104
come with a ton of ultra-fast memory
and storage.

1720
01:41:44,137 --> 01:41:48,509
iPadOS 16 adds support
for virtual memory swap,

1721
01:41:48,542 --> 01:41:50,310
meaning your iPad storage can be used

1722
01:41:50,344 --> 01:41:53,380
to expand the available memory
for all apps

1723
01:41:53,413 --> 01:41:58,752
and delivers up to 16 GB of memory
to the most demanding apps.

1724
01:41:58,785 --> 01:42:02,723
With technologies like display scaling
and virtual memory swap,

1725
01:42:02,756 --> 01:42:07,294
we have the foundation for a big leap
forward in user experience,

1726
01:42:07,327 --> 01:42:12,332
one that can change how our Pro users
get work done on iPad.

1727
01:42:12,366 --> 01:42:14,801
So we're bringing Stage Manager,

1728
01:42:14,835 --> 01:42:20,040
our latest windowing system
that you just saw in macOS, to iPadOS.

1729
01:42:20,073 --> 01:42:24,144
Stage Manager takes multitasking
on iPad to a whole new level

1730
01:42:24,178 --> 01:42:29,416
by making it more nimble and unlocking
full external display support.

1731
01:42:29,449 --> 01:42:31,218
I'd like to show it to you now.

1732
01:42:32,819 --> 01:42:34,988
Today on iPad, when you use apps,

1733
01:42:35,022 --> 01:42:38,325
you get the full screen experience
that we're all familiar with,

1734
01:42:38,358 --> 01:42:40,194
like in Photos here.

1735
01:42:40,227 --> 01:42:44,531
With Stage Manager activated,
I can now resize windows,

1736
01:42:44,565 --> 01:42:48,669
exposing a powerful new way
to work with apps on iPad.

1737
01:42:48,702 --> 01:42:52,673
And the Dock is visible,
so I can easily get to all my apps.

1738
01:42:52,706 --> 01:42:54,741
Let's open Music.

1739
01:42:54,775 --> 01:42:58,178
You'll notice that all my recently used
apps appear on the left,

1740
01:42:58,212 --> 01:43:01,048
so switching between them is really fast.

1741
01:43:01,081 --> 01:43:04,618
And Stage Manager gives me
powerful new layout capabilities

1742
01:43:04,651 --> 01:43:07,187
to create my ideal workspace.

1743
01:43:07,221 --> 01:43:11,592
For the first time on iPad,
I can work with overlapping windows.

1744
01:43:11,625 --> 01:43:16,730
I'm gonna drag Messages
alongside Calendar here,

1745
01:43:16,763 --> 01:43:20,033
and Stage Manager automatically moves
Calendar gently off to the side

1746
01:43:20,067 --> 01:43:21,902
as I bring it to the stage.

1747
01:43:21,935 --> 01:43:25,372
And if I move Messages to the left,

1748
01:43:25,405 --> 01:43:29,910
Stage Manager repositions Calendar for me
automatically.

1749
01:43:29,943 --> 01:43:32,779
And like you saw earlier,
I can resize windows

1750
01:43:32,813 --> 01:43:36,383
and arrange everything
just the way I want.

1751
01:43:36,416 --> 01:43:38,118
And it gets even better

1752
01:43:38,151 --> 01:43:42,122
when I plug my iPad
into an external display.

1753
01:43:43,857 --> 01:43:47,261
My wallpaper beautifully fills
the entire display,

1754
01:43:47,294 --> 01:43:51,098
and I can move my cursor to it
from my iPad.

1755
01:43:51,131 --> 01:43:55,169
I have the Dock here too,
so let's go ahead and launch Keynote.

1756
01:43:55,202 --> 01:43:58,405
When I do,
I once again enter Stage Manager,

1757
01:43:58,438 --> 01:44:01,241
now on an even bigger canvas.

1758
01:44:01,275 --> 01:44:03,944
All of that additional screen real estate
is so useful

1759
01:44:03,977 --> 01:44:06,580
when working on a presentation in Keynote.

1760
01:44:06,613 --> 01:44:09,082
And it's amazing when you're working
with a set of apps.

1761
01:44:09,116 --> 01:44:13,854
I can create groups of three
and even four windows.

1762
01:44:13,887 --> 01:44:16,123
This is just incredibly powerful.

1763
01:44:16,156 --> 01:44:19,026
Between my iPad and my external display,

1764
01:44:19,059 --> 01:44:23,130
I can have up to eight apps
running onscreen simultaneously.

1765
01:44:23,163 --> 01:44:28,235
And I can take advantage of the unique
capabilities of each of these displays.

1766
01:44:28,268 --> 01:44:31,205
For instance,
I'm working on this Keynote document,

1767
01:44:31,238 --> 01:44:34,541
and I want to add a drawing from Procreate

1768
01:44:34,575 --> 01:44:37,845
here on my iPad.

1769
01:44:37,878 --> 01:44:41,515
I can use Apple Pencil
to add a finishing touch

1770
01:44:41,548 --> 01:44:43,417
to my drawing.

1771
01:44:48,255 --> 01:44:51,024
And now I can jump back into the gallery

1772
01:44:51,058 --> 01:44:56,263
and then drag and drop across displays
and into my deck.

1773
01:44:56,296 --> 01:45:00,367
And that's a quick look at Stage Manager.

1774
01:45:00,400 --> 01:45:04,671
It's an entirely new way to multitask
with multiple overlapping windows,

1775
01:45:04,705 --> 01:45:08,208
flexible window sets,
fast app switching,

1776
01:45:08,242 --> 01:45:11,278
and full external display support.

1777
01:45:11,311 --> 01:45:14,147
And that's iPadOS 16,

1778
01:45:14,181 --> 01:45:17,985
a big release with exciting updates
to many of the built-in apps;

1779
01:45:18,018 --> 01:45:20,087
Weather app comes to iPad,

1780
01:45:20,120 --> 01:45:22,856
new ways to collaborate
and be productive,

1781
01:45:22,890 --> 01:45:26,560
great features for pro users,
including Stage Manager,

1782
01:45:26,593 --> 01:45:28,595
and so much more.

1783
01:45:28,629 --> 01:45:31,398
Now, back to Tim.

1784
01:45:31,431 --> 01:45:32,933
Tim: Thank you, Craig.

1785
01:45:32,966 --> 01:45:35,435
And thanks to all of our presenters.

1786
